place.name: DUNHOLME
place.gazetteerText: DUNHOLM, a parish in the district and county of Lincoln; near the source of the Langworth river, 2½ miles WNW of Langworth r. station, and 6 NNE of Lincoln. Post town, Hackthorn, under Lincoln. Acres, 2, 190. Real property, £4, 522. Pop., 453. Houses, 106. Dunholm Lodge is a chief residence. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £98. Patron, the Prebendary of Dunholm. The church is ancient; has an embattled tower; and contains some monuments. There are a Wesleyan chapel, and charities £4. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
